Merge pull request #348 from apptentive/proguard-fix ANDROID-687 Remove google library rules from consumerProguardFiles. T

ANDROID-687 Remove google library rules from consumerProguardFiles. The original purpose to have those rules was to facilitate host app that may run into proguard issue when importing libraries with support libraries dependency (See Google  Issue 78293). But by including those rules for the app we may as well overstep on the app who does not want to keep all support libraries in their app proguard. The approach we decide to tak on going forward is to exlude all support libraries from our consumer proguard, and let the host app add to the its progauard specific rules as needed.

AND-172 Add Who Card persistency check: A boolean shared preference is introduced to track if the Who-Card is ever sent.  If email is required, this oolean will only be set true if the email address is valid and sent; If email is not required, no email validation will be imposed, and both skip and send actions will set the boolean to be true.

What's more:
1. If Who Card is being edited, rotating device will save and restore the states.
2. If Who Card is sent, the name/email/avatar file id will be saved to sharedpreference. Subsequent editing will prepopulate the values from the saved ones.

AND-145 Add unread message badge as a stylable widget There are three ways of cutomizing the badge widget

1. Using theme:

In the app style.xml, first define a custom badge style

<style name="AppTheme.Badge" parent=ApptentiveMessageCenterBadge">

    <item name=counterColor>@color/cutom_color</item>
</style>
Then assign this style to attribute apptentiveMessageCenterBadgeStyle

<style name="AppTheme" parent="android:Theme">
    <item name=apptentiveMessageCenterBadgeStyle">@style/AppTheme.Badge>
 </item>
</style>

2. Customizing in layout.xml:
<com.apptentive.android.sdk.widget.ApptentiveMessageCenterBadge
    android:id="@+id/badge"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    />
<com.apptentive.android.sdk.widget.ApptentiveMessageCenterBadge
    android:id="@+id/badge2"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    apptentive:badgeSize="mini"
    apptentive:counterColor="@color/badge_text_color"
    />

3. at run time:
ApptentiveMessageCenterBadge badge = (ApptentiveMessageCenterBadge ) findViewById(R.id.badge);
fab.setSize(FloatingActionButton.SIZE_MINI);
fab.setTextColor(Color.WHITE);
